nowledged and considered. A wide range of situations involving humans and nonhuman animals are discussed, including hunting and fishing; eating and wearing; circuses, rodeos, zoos, and aquariums; scientific experimentation; and the threats of human technology and population growth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aHuman ecology -- Religious aspects. 0aHuman ecologyxReligious aspects. 0aPhilosophy of nature. 4aPhilosophy : Animal Rights. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438446714423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438446714/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles